After prosecutors dropped their bid for a death penalty, David Kaczynski, told an interviewer with visible relief: ``It feels to me like the weight of the world has gone off my shoulders.''
``The horror is with us now, and I very much doubt that it will ever leave us completely.''
``Someone we love went over the edge _ or so it seems,'' he said later.
Burdened by a terrible truth, but fearing that more innocent people could be hurt, he denounced his brother to the FBI.
